#whptelephone pic of the day!\n I have really loved taking these as I have an age old love of the telephone kiosks designed by Sir Giles Gilbert Scott. These K2's, unlike the slimline K6's, are all listed buildings. Sir Giles Gilbert Scott also designed Battersea Power Station and the Tate Modern and his father ( Sir Gilbert Scott ) designed the St Pancras building...which still has a telephone box standing proudly outside.
